edu.ncsu.csc216.pack_scheduler.util

Class LinkedAbstractList<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
      • java.util.AbstractList<E>
        • edu.ncsu.csc216.pack_scheduler.util.LinkedAbstractList<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - The object type that the list will manage.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<E>, java.util.Collection<E>, java.util.List<E>

    public class LinkedAbstractList<E>
extends java.util.AbstractList<E>
    Class defines state and behavior for a custom LinkedAbstractList class that does not allow duplicates or null elements. Used for CourseRoll to manage the list of Students registered for a Course. Class implements AbstractList methods for get, set, add, remove, and size.
    Author:
    Nick Garner
